1NT pass 2D pass 2H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "fcf513047d7b53744b4c1e1ccefddcbba189a9cd16f0e1a8eb90b265cd83f1c8"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{East opens 1NT.  

You should bid 2\D to transfer partner to \Hs. He bids 2\H.  

You know you have at least an 8-card \H fit. You know you have at least 26 points (15 + 11). She who knows, goes, so you bid 4\H.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "N:QJ5.K8.AT62.AK98 43.QJT5.KQ754.JT KT987.A9764.83.5 A62.32.J9.Q76432"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1NT pass 2D pass 2H pass 2S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "a6dcb0f5282592930278916cae6d2a7af437d959b8a0031c58b14301d65a96ed"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_transfers"]
[Student "S"]
{North opens 1NT.  

You transfer of course, but to which Major? It can work either way, but the preferred method is to first transfer partner to \Hs when you have an invitational hand. So you bid 2\D, and partner of course says 2\H.  

You now show your second 5-card Major by bidding 2\S.

At this point partner becomes the Captain. You have described an invitational (9 point) hand with 5-5 in the Majors. Partner's next bid should set the contract wherever he chooses. In this case, with a maximum 1NT opener and 3 \Ss he picks 4\S.

Note that you must have at least one Major suit fit since partner cannot have a doubleton in both.}

